Package nl.codevs.strinput.system

Annotation Interface StrInput

@Retention(RUNTIME) @Target({METHOD,TYPE}) public @interface StrInput
Annotation for commands (methods) and categories (classes).
Note that while all settings are optional, name() should be specified on a category.
Since:
v0.1

  • Element Details

    • name

      String name
      The name of this command, which is the Method's name by default.
      Returns:
      the name of the command / category
      Default:
      ""

    • aliases

      String[] aliases
      The aliases of this parameter (instead of just the name (if specified) or Method Name (name of method))
      Can be initialized as just a string (ex. "alias") or as an array (ex. {"alias1", "alias2"})
      If someone uses /plugin foo, and you specify alias="f" here, /plugin f will do the exact same.
      Returns:
      the aliases of this StrInput
      Default:
      {""}

    • description

      String description
      The description of this command.
      Is DEFAULT_DESCRIPTION by default
      Returns:
      the description of this StrInput
      Default:
      "No Description Provided"

    • permission

      String permission
      The permissions class that gives the required permission for this command.

      By default, it requires no permissions

      Returns:
      The permission node for this decree command
      Default:
      "No Permission Required"

    • sync

      boolean sync
      If the node's functions MUST be run in sync, set this to true.
      Defaults to false
      Returns:
      true if this category's commands or command should be run in sync
      Default:
      false
